      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 503: This removes the previous DispatchQueue.main.async boundary, but the new code instantiates a UIViewController and then performs modal/navigation work. If startOutgoingCall is invoked off the main thread, this can touch UIKit from a background thread and crash or create intermittent UI corruption. Keep the new ordering, but execute it on the main queue.\n```suggestion\n        DispatchQueue.main.async { [weak self] in\n            guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n\n            let callViewController \u003d CallViewController.instantiate(with: self.injectionBag)\n            callViewController.viewModel.placeCall(with: contactRingId,\n                                                   userName: userName,\n                                                   account: account,\n                                                   isAudioOnly: isAudioOnly)\n\n            self.dismissAllModals { [weak self] in\n                guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n                self.popToSmartList()\n                self.navigateToConversationIfNeeded(for: contactRingId, account: account)\n                self.present(viewController: callViewController,\n                             withStyle: .fadeInOverFullScreen,\n                             withAnimation: false,\n                             withStateable: callViewController.viewModel)\n            }\n        }\n```",
